## **Overview of Front-end Frameworks**

Front-end frameworks are programming language tools that are used to simplify and organize the process of web development.

They are a form of computing development architecture that offers structures, design patterns, and code blocks that developers can reuse to develop and build complex user interfaces more efficiently.

**The key reasons for using front-end frameworks include:**

## **Modularity**

Developing modular components is an important aspect of front-end frameworks, as they make it possible to work on large complex user interfaces by splitting their scope into smaller parts, which can later be used repeatedly.

Modularity makes collaboration easier because a team of developers can work on different components of the system simultaneously. It also enhances web organization, scalability and maintenance.

## **Efficiency**

Front-end frameworks provide a structured web architecture during the web development process, ensuring consistent flow across the web application interface.

A structured framework enhances aesthetics and navigation across the web application, which positively impacts users’ experience and meaningful engagements.

## **Responsive Design**

